<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1400,2039]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,501]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="142" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,325,1400,1426]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Redescription.</emphasis>
In addition to the characters of the genus: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[815,882,1400,1426]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Male.</emphasis>
Medium size (
<quantity box="[1054,1183,1400,1427]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="140" unit="mm" value="30.0" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="25.0">25–35 mm</quantity>
.), body reddish-brown shiny (
<figureCitation box="[226,360,1436,1462]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,415,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-89@2.[151,1436,414,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cratomelus armatus male habitus. A. Lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Head and thorax in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919888/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Figs. 1A–B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[378,449,1436,1462]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Head.</emphasis>
Fastigium of vertex not projected, almost as wide as scapus. Fastigium of frons rounded, touching fastigium of vertex. Clypeus wider than high, subtriangular, lateral margin gradually narrowing towards apical margin, slightly curved; apical margin arched. Scapus and pedicellus unarmed (
<figureCitation box="[1127,1216,1508,1534]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,415,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-89@2.[151,1436,414,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cratomelus armatus male habitus. A. Lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Head and thorax in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919888/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1238,1333,1508,1534]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotal disc with rounded anterior and posterior border, anterior border covered with short hairs (
<figureCitation box="[1149,1238,1544,1570]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,415,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-89@2.[151,1436,414,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cratomelus armatus male habitus. A. Lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Head and thorax in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919888/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1259,1322,1544,1570]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Legs.</emphasis>
Fore tibia with a spur on the inner dorsal margin, near the apex, three or four spurs on both ventral margins, and apex with two spurs of similar length (
<figureCitation box="[420,511,1616,1642]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Mid-tibia with two spurs on the outer dorsal margin and three spurs on the inner dorsal margin, ventral margins with four spurs, and apex with two spurs similar in length on each side (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1423,1652,1678]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Hind femur with granules on dorsal margin; outer face of the femur with 12-16 chevrons located in the upper half, occupying two-thirds of the length of the femur; genicular lobe armed with a spinule on the ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[1336,1424,1724,1750]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Hind tibia with six conspicuous spines on each dorsal margin, ventral margins with two or three small spurs, apex with three spurs on each side, the most prominent being the dorsal ones (
<figureCitation box="[971,1105,1796,1822]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Figs. 2D–E</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1123,1206,1796,1822]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Wings.</emphasis>
Tegminae surpasses the first abdominal tergite, reaching about the middle of the abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[963,1054,1832,1858]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,415,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-89@2.[151,1436,414,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cratomelus armatus male habitus. A. Lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Head and thorax in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919888/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Dorsal edge of tegmina curved, ventral one straight, widened area between MP+CuA2 with ten to twelve transversal veins (
<figureCitation box="[1161,1245,1868,1894]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
). Hind wing with thickened veins, with two markedly expanded areas, the first and most conspicuous between the Sc and R veins, ovoid and elongated, the dorsal edge after this area is surrounded by Sc branches. The second area, between the CuP vein and the anal veins, is elongated and lanceolate (
<figureCitation box="[755,847,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[868,985,1976,2002]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Abdomen</emphasis>
robust, posterior margin of 6th and 7th tergites angulated, projecting moderately. 8th tergite extends over the last abdominal tergites, and is slightly divided at apex (
<figureCitation box="[222,314,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">Fig. 2H</figureCitation>
). 9th tergite with rounded posterior border and projecting moderately over last segment (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1418,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
I- K). 10th tergite slightly divided by a membranous area, with a conical hook on each side (
<figureCitation box="[1183,1264,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">Fig. 2I</figureCitation>
). Cerci simple, projecting upwards from the base towards the apex (
<figureCitation box="[727,807,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">Fig. 2J</figureCitation>
). Paraprocts flattened, thin flexible, in the form of a wide hook (
<figureCitation box="[221,339,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">Figs. 2I, L</figureCitation>
). Male subgenital plate notch deep, reaching half the total length of the subgenital plate and covered by hairs along the edge of the notch; stily cylindrical and with almost the same thickness throughout its length (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1623,1647]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[151,1437,181,1599]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cratomelus armatus male. A. Fore and B. Middle legs. C. hind femur. D and E. Hind tibia in lateral and dorsal view. F. Tegmina. G. Hind wing. H–K. Terminalia in dorsal, axial, lateral and ventral view respectively. L. paraproct and cerci. (The red arrows in figures F and G, show the wing veins modification. The white arrow in figure I, show the hook of the last tergite)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919892/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">Fig. 2K</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,397,330,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">Phallic complex</emphasis>
almost membranous, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[643,673,331,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">dl.</emphasis>
lanceolate with an angulated posterior edge (
<figureCitation box="[1179,1269,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1851,1875]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1827]" captionTargetId="figure-28@5.[151,1435,181,1827]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cratomelus armatus male genitalia. A. Dorsal. B. Ventral. C. Axial and D. Inside views respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919894/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1289,1320,331,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">ldl</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1374,1436,331,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">lw.vl.</emphasis>
located sideways (
<figureCitation box="[360,496,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1851,1875]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1827]" captionTargetId="figure-28@5.[151,1435,181,1827]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cratomelus armatus male genitalia. A. Dorsal. B. Ventral. C. Axial and D. Inside views respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919894/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">Figs. 3A–B</figureCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[517,548,367,393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">ldl</emphasis>
rounded, in the middle of these is located 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1037,1054,366,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">ti</emphasis>
, which is moderately sclerotized, yellowish, and located on the inner borders of 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[667,698,403,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">ldl</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[713,845,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1851,1875]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1827]" captionTargetId="figure-28@5.[151,1435,181,1827]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cratomelus armatus male genitalia. A. Dorsal. B. Ventral. C. Axial and D. Inside views respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919894/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">Figs. 3B–C</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[864,919,403,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">lw.vl</emphasis>
located, in ventral view, quadrangular, shorter than 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[205,236,439,465]" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">ldl</emphasis>
, and covered by numerous microstructures (
<figureCitation box="[730,827,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1851,1875]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1827]" captionTargetId="figure-28@5.[151,1435,181,1827]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cratomelus armatus male genitalia. A. Dorsal. B. Ventral. C. Axial and D. Inside views respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919894/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">Figs. 3B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[847,889,438,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">Ejv</emphasis>
rounded and medium-sized; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1212,1249,438,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">ejd</emphasis>
thin and tubular, without sclerotizations (
<figureCitation box="[421,511,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1851,1875]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1827]" captionTargetId="figure-28@5.[151,1435,181,1827]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cratomelus armatus male genitalia. A. Dorsal. B. Ventral. C. Axial and D. Inside views respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919894/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[531,561,474,500]" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">Df</emphasis>
thin and surrounding the anterior border of the genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1206,1332,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1851,1875]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1827]" captionTargetId="figure-28@5.[151,1435,181,1827]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cratomelus armatus male genitalia. A. Dorsal. B. Ventral. C. Axial and D. Inside views respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6919894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6919894/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="142">Fig. 3A–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
